CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1958, reads: "Leo J. McLaughlin...wins another term." Partial article reads: "In the Fifth Legislative District, Republican Walter C. Rainey lost to Democrat Leo J. McLaughlin by slightly less than two to one. Rainey's surprising vote came from the few Republicans in 12th and 13th wards and the increased number of dissatisfied Negro Democratic votes in the district."
TitMainTitle: Leo J. McLaughlin, Democratic candidate for the legislature in the Fifth District, exiting voting machine
